+            // ensure removing items are below non-removing ones, and provide
+            // a deterministic stacking among items (based on index) so that
+            // simultaneous removals behave predictably.
+            //
+            // Strategy:
+            //  - non-removing items get a large base z so they are always on top
+            //  - removing items get small (or negative) z values so they are below
+            //  - among removing items, lower index is given a higher z so earlier
+            //    items appear above later ones (this matches the desired behavior
+            //    where the first item remains above a removing second item)
+            z: (isRemoving ? -index : (10000 - index))
